3.4.3 Psychological effect
3.4.3.1 Cage logic
Apple Co. for example: A free trial and Fee-based value-added services
Xiaomi phones for example
3.4.3.2 BJ Fogg's behavior model
Effectively look for behavioral reasons for three elements: motivation, ability and trigger
B=MAT
four steps:
    1> trigger(internal and external)
    2> behave(touch and use)
    3> Variable motivation(social and games)
    4> input to form a habit
3.4.3.3 Flow theory
flow theory is immersion experience
the core theory is that people achieve this when their skills match their challenges

